Type: Package
Package: SpaDES.targets
Title: Orchestrate SpaDES Simulations with 'targets'
Version: 0.0.0.9005
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alex M", "Chubaty", , "achubaty@for-cast.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7146-8135"))
  )
Description: Helpers to run 'SpaDES' simulations (simInitAndSpades) as stages of
    a 'targets' pipeline. Each stage runs in-process and, instead of serializing
    the whole simList, returns a manifest of the files it saved -- discovered
    dynamically from 'outputs(sim)', which captures per-timestep saves,
    module-registered outputs, and 'Plots()' figures alike -- exposed as a
    'format = "file"' target so 'targets' tracks them and a downstream stage
    reloads them via its own 'inputs'. Also provides a hard options "firewall"
    that disables the known-destructive 'reproducible'/'SpaDES.core' behaviours,
    plus spatial file-target and provenance helpers.
